  "text": "where y � p/p u , x � s/s 0 , and B 4 � 1.6(A 4 − 1)2. s 0 is the value of slip corresponding to the peak load, and s 0 � 100/d. e ascending parameter A 4 is defined as the ratio of bond stiffness to peak secant stiffness, and A 4 � (10d − 80) /(0.7d − 5). p u is the shear capacity per stud. For a slip up to 5 mm, V reaches 99% of the ultimate load V u . When the longitudinal, lateral, and vertical stiffness adopt expression [CITATION_1] in this paper, good results can be obtained.",
